{
  "doc_id": "22810",
  "text": "Distribution ratios of radioactivity, the ratio of cpm/ml of intracellular fluid to cpm/rnl of incubation medium, were calculated as described previously [CITATION_1] . The intracellular fluid volume was calculated as the difference between the total tissue fluid (wet weight minus dry weight after overnight desiccation) and the volume of \"trapped fluid.\" The trapped fluid volume was determined using ['4C]polyethylene glycol as previously described [CITATION_2] .",
